article.description: Three players scored in double figures for UCF as the Knights defeated SMU 69-53 in the first round of the Conference USA tournament Wednesday night.
article.headline: Young, Sosa, Tyler give UCF scoring edge over SMU
article.linkText: UCF topples SMU in Conference USA tourney

article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Three players scored in double figures for UCF as the Knights defeated SMU 69-53 in the first round of the Conference USA tournament Wednesday night. Taylor Young scored 15 points, Isaac Sosa 14 and A. J. Tyler 12 for ninth-seeded UCF (15-16), which will play UTEP (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP), the tournament's top seed, in the quarterfinals Thursday night. The Knights were 5-for-12 from 3-point range in the first half in taking a 32-30 lead. The eighth-seeded Mustangs (14-17) led 18-11 early, but UCF went on a 17-4 run and continued the momentum in the second half. Keith Clanton scored off his own rebound while getting fouled on the play, and hit a free throw for a three-point play for a 46-36 lead. Marcus Jordan, the son of NBA great Michael Jordan, made it 65-50 with a three-point play. Derek Williams led SMU with 15 points.
